  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>A body of mass 1 kg is suspended by a weightless string which passes over a frictionless pulley of mass 2 kg as shown in the figure. The mass is released from a height of 1.6 m from the ground. With what velocity does it strike the ground?</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m5w5hjvc/b2925d17-fb81-4d99-b5e5-d2cdd6c646e9/07066580-d249-11ef-80d9-bd33a9c6e008/file-jaoe38c1m5w5hjvd.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m5w5hjvc/b2925d17-fb81-4d99-b5e5-d2cdd6c646e9/07066580-d249-11ef-80d9-bd33a9c6e008/file-jaoe38c1m5w5hjvd.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2024 Physics - Rotational Motion Question 3 English\"></p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": " $16 \\mathrm{~ms}^{-1}$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": " $8 \\mathrm{~ms}^{-1}$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": " $4 \\sqrt{2} \\mathrm{~ms}^{-1}$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": " $4 \\mathrm{~ms}^{-1}$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Given, mass of the body, $m_1=1 \\mathrm{~kg}$</p>\n<p>Mass of pulley, $m_2=2 \\mathrm{~kg}$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m5w5j69w/8847a516-d40e-46f2-a169-2207cf56b289/34241440-d249-11ef-80d9-bd33a9c6e008/file-jaoe38c1m5w5j69x.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m5w5j69w/8847a516-d40e-46f2-a169-2207cf56b289/34241440-d249-11ef-80d9-bd33a9c6e008/file-jaoe38c1m5w5j69x.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2024 Physics - Rotational Motion Question 3 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n&amp;\\text { According to conservation of energy, }\\\\\n&amp;\\begin{aligned}\nm_1 g h &amp; =\\frac{1}{2} m_1 v^2+\\frac{1}{2} I \\omega^2 \\\\\n&amp; =\\frac{1}{2} \\omega_1 v^2+\\frac{1}{2} \\times \\frac{m_2 R^2}{2} \\times\\left(\\frac{v}{R}\\right)^2\n\\end{aligned}\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>\n<p>$\\left[\\because I=\\frac{m_2 R^2}{2}\\right.$ and $\\left.\\omega=\\frac{v}{R}\\right]$</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n&amp; \\Rightarrow \\quad m_1 g h=\\frac{1}{2} m_1 v^2+\\frac{1}{4} \\times m_2 v^2 \\\\\n&amp; \\Rightarrow 1 \\times 10 \\times 1.6=\\frac{1}{2} \\times 1 \\times v^2+\\frac{1}{4} \\times 2 \\times v^2 \\\\\n&amp; \\Rightarrow \\quad v^2=4 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>",
    "topic": "combined-translational-and-rotational-motion",
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2024",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The moment of inertia of a rigid body about an axis</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "does not depend on its mass.\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "does not depend on its shape.\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "depends on the position of axis of rotation.\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "does not depend on its size."
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Moment of inertia of a body depends on the mass of the body, distribution of mass in the body, position of axis of rotation of the body and on the distance from the axis of rotation.</p>",
    "topic": "moment-of-inertia",
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2023",
    "difficulty": null
