    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The angular speed of a motor wheel is increased from $$1200 \\mathrm{~rpm}$$ to $$3120 \\mathrm{~rpm}$$ in $$16 \\mathrm{~s}$$. The angular acceleration of the motor wheel is</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "$$4 \\pi \\mathrm{~rad} / \\mathrm{s}^2$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$$6 \\pi \\mathrm{~rad} / \\mathrm{s}^2$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "$$8 \\pi \\mathrm{~rad} / \\mathrm{s}^2$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "$$2 \\pi \\mathrm{~rad} / \\mathrm{s}^2$$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Given, initial angular frequency of wheel,</p>\n<p>$$f_0=1200 \\mathrm{rpm}=\\frac{1200}{60} \\mathrm{rps}=20 \\mathrm{~rps}$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ Initial angular velocity,</p>\n<p>$$\\omega_0=2 \\pi f_0=2 \\pi \\times 20=40 \\pi \\mathrm{rad} / \\mathrm{s}$$</p>\n<p>Similarly, final angular speed,</p>\n<p>$$\\omega=2 \\pi \\times\\left(\\frac{3120}{60}\\right) \\mathrm{rad} / \\mathrm{s}=104 \\pi \\mathrm{rad} / \\mathrm{s}$$</p>\n<p>$$\\text { Time, } \\quad t=16 \\mathrm{~s}$$</p>\n<p>If $$\\alpha$$ be the angular acceleration of the wheel, then</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\omega & =\\omega_0+\\alpha t \\\\\n\\Rightarrow \\quad \\alpha & =\\frac{\\omega-\\omega_0}{t}=\\frac{104 \\pi-40 \\pi}{16} \\\\\n& =\\frac{64 \\pi}{16}=4 \\pi \\mathrm{~rad} / \\mathrm{s}^2\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>",
    "topic": "rotational-motion-about-fixed-axis-of-rigid-body",
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2022",
    "difficulty": null
  },
