    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>In figure $$E$$ and $$v_{\\mathrm{cm}}$$ represent the total energy and speed of centre of mass of an object of mass $$1 \\mathrm{~kg}$$ in pure rolling. The object is</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lt9v5bw7/03f9982e-5e9e-458e-a55a-3fc36bde822d/c1074870-d874-11ee-aba2-450d22ee9eaf/file-1lt9v5bw8.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lt9v5bw7/03f9982e-5e9e-458e-a55a-3fc36bde822d/c1074870-d874-11ee-aba2-450d22ee9eaf/file-1lt9v5bw8.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2021 Physics - Rotational Motion Question 8 English\"></p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "sphere"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "ring"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "disc"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "hollow cylinder"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>As we know, kinetic energy of an object in pure rolling motion is given as</p>\n<p>$$E=\\frac{1}{2} m v_{\\mathrm{cm}}^2\\left(1+\\frac{k^2}{R^2}\\right)$$</p>\n<p>where, $$k$$ is radius of gyration and $m$ is the mass of the object.</p>\n<p>$$\\Rightarrow \\quad \\frac{E}{v_{\\mathrm{cm}}^2}=\\frac{1}{2}\\left[1+\\frac{k^2}{R^2}\\right] \\quad \\text{.... (i)}$$</p>\n<p>[$$\\because$$ Given, $$m=1 \\mathrm{~kg}$$]</p>\n<p>From the given graph, substituting the value of $$\\frac{E}{v_{\\mathrm{cin}}^2}$$ in Eq. (i), we get</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\frac{3}{4} & =\\frac{1}{2}\\left[1+\\frac{k^2}{R^2}\\right] \\\\\n\\frac{3}{2}-1 & =\\frac{k^2}{R^2} \\\\\n\\frac{k^2}{R^2} & =\\frac{1}{2}\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>\n<p>Since, for a</p>\n<p>(a) Sphere, $$\\frac{k^2}{R^2}=\\frac{2}{5}$$</p>\n<p>(b) Ring, $$\\frac{k^2}{R^2}=1$$</p>\n<p>(c) Hollow cylinder, $$\\frac{k^2}{R^2}=1$$</p>\n<p>(d) Disc, $$\\frac{k^2}{R^2}=\\frac{1}{2}$$</p>\n<p>So, the given object is disc.</p>",
    "topic": "combined-translational-and-rotational-motion",
    "year": 2021,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2021",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>A wheel starting from rest gains an angular velocity of $$10 \\mathrm{~rad} / \\mathrm{s}$$ after uniformly accelerated for $$5 \\mathrm{~s}$$. The total angle through which it has turned is</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "$$25 \\mathrm{~rad}$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$$100 \\mathrm{~rad}$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "$$25 \\pi \\mathrm{~rad}$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "$$50 \\pi \\mathrm{~rad}$$ and a vertical axis"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Initial angular velocity of wheel, $$\\omega_0=0$$</p>\n<p>Final angular velocity, $$\\omega=10 \\mathrm{rad} / \\mathrm{s}$$</p>\n<p>$$t=5 \\mathrm{~s}$$</p>\n<p>By first equation of rotational motion,</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\omega=\\omega_0+\\alpha t \\\\\n\\Rightarrow \\quad & 10=0+\\alpha \\times 5 \\\\\n\\Rightarrow \\quad & \\alpha=\\frac{10}{5}=2 \\mathrm{rad} / \\mathrm{s}^2\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>\n<p>If $$\\theta$$ be the total angle through which wheel has turned, then from,</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\theta & =\\omega_0 t+\\frac{1}{2} \\alpha t^2 \\\\\n& =0 \\times 5+\\frac{1}{2} \\times 2 \\times 5^2=0+25 \\\\\n\\Rightarrow \\quad \\theta & =25 \\mathrm{rad}\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>",
    "topic": "rotational-motion-about-fixed-axis-of-rigid-body",
    "year": 2020,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2020",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>A thin uniform rectangular plate of mass $$2 \\mathrm{~kg}$$ is placed in $$x y$$-plane as shown in figure. The moment of inertial about $$x$$-axis is $$I_x=0.2 \\mathrm{~kgm}^2$$ and the moment of inertia about $$Y$$-axis is $$I_y=0.3 \\mathrm{~kgm}^2$$. The radius of gyration of the plate about the axis passing through $$O$$ and perpendicular to the plane of the plate is</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lth0xbwe/f6a72fd8-3f9f-4922-97c9-a5767cd54579/d5e159e0-dc64-11ee-9f99-f3a00dbfa5f2/file-1lth0xbwf.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lth0xbwe/f6a72fd8-3f9f-4922-97c9-a5767cd54579/d5e159e0-dc64-11ee-9f99-f3a00dbfa5f2/file-1lth0xbwf.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2020 Physics - Rotational Motion Question 6 English\"></p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "50 cm"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "5 cm"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "38.7 cm"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "31.6 cm"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Given, mass, $$M=2 \\mathrm{~kg}$$</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n& I_x=0.2 \\mathrm{~kg}-\\mathrm{m}^2 \\\\\n& I_y=0.3 \\mathrm{~kg}-\\mathrm{m}^2\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>\n<p>and $$I_y=0.3 \\mathrm{~kg}-\\mathrm{m}^2$$</p>\n<p>According to the perpendicular axis theorem, the moment of inertia of the rectangular plate about an axis passing through $$O$$ and perpendicular to the plane of plate is</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\nI & =I_x+I_y=0.2+0.3 \\\\\n& =0.5 \\mathrm{~kg} \\mathrm{~m}^2\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>\n<p>Also, $$\\quad I=M k^2$$</p>\n<p>where, $$k=$$ radius of gyration.</p>\n<p>$$\\Rightarrow \\quad k=\\sqrt{\\frac{I}{M}}=\\sqrt{\\frac{0.5}{2}}=\\sqrt{0.25}=0.5 \\mathrm{~m} \\text { or } 50 \\mathrm{~cm}$$</p>",
