    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "Moment of inertia of a body about two perpendicular axes $X$ and $Y$ in the plane of lamina are $20 \\mathrm{~kg}-\\mathrm{m}^2$ and $25 \\mathrm{~kg}-\\mathrm{m}^2$, respectively. Its moment of inertia about an axis perpendicular to the plane of the lamina and passing through the point of intersection of $X$ and $Y$-axes is\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "$5 \\mathrm{~kg}-\\mathrm{m}^2$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$45 \\mathrm{~kg}-\\mathrm{m}^2$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "$12.5 \\mathrm{~kg}-\\mathrm{m}^2$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "$500 \\mathrm{~kg}-\\mathrm{m}^2$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>To solve this problem, we use the perpendicular axis theorem. This theorem is applicable to flat, planar objects (laminae) and states that the moment of inertia about an axis perpendicular to the plane (say the z-axis) is the sum of the moments of inertia about two mutually perpendicular axes (x and y) lying in the plane. Here’s how to apply this theorem:</p>\n\n<p><p>According to the perpendicular axis theorem:</p>\n<p>$$I_z = I_x + I_y$$</p></p>\n<p><p>Substitute the given values:</p>\n<p>$$I_z = 20 \\, \\text{kg-m}^2 + 25 \\, \\text{kg-m}^2 = 45 \\, \\text{kg-m}^2$$</p></p>\n\n<p>Thus, the moment of inertia about the axis perpendicular to the plane is $$45 \\, \\text{kg-m}^2.$$ </p>\n<p>The correct answer is Option B.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2018,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2018",
    "difficulty": null
  }
